name: opt_einsum_fx
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "opt_einsum_fx" %}
{% set version = "0.1.4" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/opt_einsum_fx-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 7eeb7f91ecb70be65e6179c106ea7f64fc1db6319e3d1289a4518b384f81e74f

build:
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  number: 0

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.6
  run:
    - opt-einsum
    - packaging
    - python >=3.6
    - pytorch >=1.8.0

test:
  imports:
    - opt_einsum_fx
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/Linux-cpp-lisp/opt_einsum_fx
  summary: Einsum optimization using opt_einsum and PyTorch FX
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - jan-janssen
